			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerTitleCompanyLabel">Director of Game Design, Midway Games (The Suffering)</span></td>
		        </tr>
		        <tr>
			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerBioLabel">Richard Rouse III is Director of Game Design at Midway Games.  Most recently, he was Creative Director and Writer on the action/horror titles The Suffering and its sequel, The Suffering: Ties That Bind.  Rouse has been developing games for over a decade and during that time has tinkered away on a number of titles, including Drakan:  The Ancients' Gates, Centipede 3D, Damage Incorporated, and Odyssey: The Legend of Nemesis.  He has written about game design for publications including Game Developer, SIGGRAPH Computer Graphics, Develop, Gamasutra, and Inside Mac Games.  Rouse's popular and sizable book about game design and development titled Game Design:  Theory & Practice was released in an expanded second edition in 2004.</span></td>
